# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to comit your .python-version file.
#   For an app, you might want to ignore it.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#1192, it is a recommended practice to commit Pipfile.lock.
#   However, if you feel differently, uncomment the following line.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   By default, poetry.lock is committed. Uncomment if you want to ignore it.
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   By default, pdm.lock is committed. Uncomment if you want to ignore it.
#pdm.lock

